First it targeted our vacuum cleaners in the name of global warming – now the EU is gunning for petrol-driven lawnmowers.

They are among a range of outdoor equipment facing stringent emissions tests, including chainsaws, combine harvesters and river barges.

The European Commission has already forced vacuum cleaner manufacturers to stop producing the most powerful machines.

